                                <condition key="deficient">
                                  The manuscript is in poor condition. There are stains of various origins and darkening around the margins.
                                  Some leaves present tears and losses, some likely caused by rodents (e.g. <locus from="10" to="12"/>).
                                  Some leaves are detached, e.g. <locus from="31" to="33"/>, <locus target="#43"/> and <locus target="#50"/>.
                                  The edges of most leaves are darkened by use and humidity. Some leaves are stained, others are torn (e.g. <locus from="10" to="13"/>).
                                  The sewing is broken, leaving only fragments of the third 'chain' on the spine intact.
                                  The back cover is split vertically in half. The two parts are held together by threads passing through pairs of holes drilled through the covers.
                                  Large tunnels formed by insects are carved into the covers.
                                  The hinging strap of the satchel is torn into two pieces.
                                </condition>
